      "id": 361029,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Attempted Grignard reaction of cyclohexanone with <i>tert</i>-butylmagnesium bromide yields only about 1% of the expected addition product along with 99% unreacted cyclohexanone. If D<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> is added to the reaction mixture after a suitable period, however, the “unreacted” cyclohexanone is found to have one deuterium atom incorporated into it. Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBa2tZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--4b804c9cdc4e01e7189706d76b9a01adb308d586/OChem_22_EC_045.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclohexanone is treated first with tert-butylmagnesium bromide and then with deuterium plus to form one percent of the expected addition product and 99 percent of alpha-deuterocyclohexanone.\">",
